Historical C/X11 sources
========================

The retained historical source files carry their original copyright notices
and license terms. In particular, the Digital Equipment Corporation notice
permits use, copying, modification, and distribution without fee provided the
copyright and permission notices are retained and the Digital name is not used
for advertising without prior written permission. The Xerox modifications
require retention of their notice and acknowledgement of the Digital and Xerox
origins. Files carrying an X Consortium notice additionally grant an
irrevocable, royalty-free right to use, copy, modify, merge, publish,
distribute, sublicense, and sell those files.

The complete original notices remain at the head of the relevant historical
files and govern those files.
